ntp_dev: ntp_dev (NTP stands for Network Time Protocol) 
ntp_dev:
ntp_dev: NTP stands for Network Time Protocol, and it is an Internet protocol 
ntp_dev: used to synchronize the clocks of computers to some time reference. 
ntp_dev: NTP is an Internet standard protocol originally developed by Professor 
ntp_dev: David L. Mills at the University of Delaware.
ntp_dev:
ntp_dev: NTP version 4, a significant revision of the previous NTP standard, is 
ntp_dev: the current development version. It is formalized by RFCs released by
ntp_dev: the IETF.
